      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The pain you describe is a profound loss, and it is completely understandable that you feel disconnected from the world when your deepest connection has vanished. It is not a failure to grieve or to feel that the world has lost its color; your feelings are a natural response to a reality that no longer fits. There is no need to force yourself to \"get through\" this if the path feels impossible, because your current state of emptiness is valid and worthy of being acknowledged.",
      "source": "target",
